headline: 1 High-Yield Dividend Stock Near a 52-Week Low to Buy in June for Passive Income
summary: Clorox’s weak guidance spooked investors.  It's been a good year for the consumer staples sector, which is outperforming the S&P 500 (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) year to date with a near 5% gain at the time of this writing.  Here's why Clorox (NYSE: CLX) stock is under pressure, and why the high-yield dividend stock is worth a closer look in June.
